(41, 1, 11, 19, 2, 7, 7, 'my beloved Son', 'Connection of Sonship', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as God''s Son. Mark 1:11 declares Him as ''my beloved Son,'' while Psalms 2:7 states, ''Thou art my Son.'' This connection highlights the affirmation of Jesus'' divine sonship.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 11, 51, 1, 13, 13, 'my beloved Son', 'Connection of Sonship and Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as the beloved Son of God. Mark highlights God''s approval of Jesus, while Colossians speaks of the kingdom belonging to His dear Son, linking their significance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 11, 61, 1, 17, 18, 'Thou art my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.', 'Divine Affirmation of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the declaration of Jesus as God''s beloved Son. The voice from heaven in Mark 1:11 is echoed in 2 Peter 1:17-18, reinforcing the significance of this divine affirmation.', 'quotation', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 11, 43, 3, 16, 16, 'my beloved Son', 'Connection of Divine Sonship', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s love for His Son and the world. Both passages emphasize the significance of Jesus as the beloved Son, linking His identity to the salvation offered to believers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 12, 40, 4, 1, 11, 'the Spirit driveth him into the wilderness', 'Wilderness Temptation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the wilderness experience of Jesus, where he is led by the Spirit. This connection highlights the significance of the Spirit''s role in guiding Jesus into a time of testing and preparation.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 12, 42, 4, 1, 13, 'the Spirit driveth him into the wilderness', 'Connection of Wilderness Temptation', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus being led into the wilderness by the Spirit. This connection highlights the significance of the wilderness as a place of testing and spiritual preparation for Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 13, 58, 2, 17, 18, 'tempted of Satan', 'Connection of Temptation and Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of temptation in both passages. Mark 1:13 describes Jesus being tempted, while Hebrews 2:17-18 emphasizes his ability to help those who are tempted due to his own experiences of suffering.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 13, 58, 4, 15, 15, 'tempted of Satan', 'Temptation and Human Experience', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of temptation, highlighting that Jesus was ''tempted of Satan'' in the wilderness and that he experienced temptation ''in all points'' like humans do. This connection underscores the shared human experience of struggle against sin.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 13, 2, 34, 28, 28, 'forty days', 'Wilderness and Divine Encounter', 'Both passages emphasize a period of forty days in the wilderness, highlighting a significant time of divine encounter and testing. The presence of God is central in both, with angels ministering in Mark and the Lord directly in Exodus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 13, 40, 26, 53, 53, 'angels ministered unto him', 'Angels in Times of Need', 'This connection highlights the role of angels in both passages. In Mark, angels minister to Jesus in the wilderness, while in Matthew, Jesus refers to the possibility of calling upon angels for assistance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 13, 5, 9, 11, 11, 'forty days', 'Connection of Forty Days', 'Both passages emphasize a period of forty days, highlighting a time of testing and divine revelation. In Mark, Jesus is tempted in the wilderness, while in Deuteronomy, Moses receives the covenant from God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 13, 5, 9, 18, 18, 'forty days', 'Connection of Temptation and Fasting', 'Both passages emphasize a period of forty days, highlighting a time of testing and spiritual struggle. In Mark, Jesus is tempted in the wilderness, while in Deuteronomy, Moses fasts for the people''s sins, showing a parallel in their experiences of trial.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 13, 11, 19, 5, 8, 'angels ministered unto him', 'Angelic Ministry in Wilderness', 'This connection highlights the presence of angels ministering in both passages. In Mark, angels minister to Jesus after his temptation, while in 1 Kings, an angel provides sustenance to Elijah during his time in the wilderness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 14, 40, 4, 23, 23, 'preaching the gospel of the kingdom', 'Jesus'' Ministry in Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ministry in Galilee, highlighting His role in preaching the gospel of the kingdom. The mention of healing in Matthew complements the preaching noted in Mark, showcasing the holistic nature of Jesus'' mission.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 14, 40, 4, 12, 12, NULL, 'Jesus'' Ministry Begins in Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' movement into Galilee following John''s imprisonment. This connection highlights the transition in Jesus'' ministry as he begins to preach the gospel.', 'parallel', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 14, 42, 8, 1, 1, 'preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God', 'Preaching the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the act of preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God. Mark 1:14 introduces Jesus'' ministry in Galilee, while Luke 8:1 describes his ongoing preaching throughout cities and villages.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 14, 23, 61, 1, 3, 'preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God', 'Connection of Preaching Good Tidings', 'This connection highlights the theme of preaching good news. Both passages emphasize the proclamation of liberty and comfort to those in need, linking Jesus'' ministry to the prophetic mission described in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 14, 49, 2, 17, 17, 'preaching the gospel of the kingdom', 'Preaching Peace and the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of preaching, as both passages emphasize the act of proclaiming a message. In Mark, Jesus preaches the gospel, while in Ephesians, the focus is on preaching peace to those near and far.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
